ls (although it is common for images to be sized appropriately using height and width in CSS):</p>\n<pre><code class="language-html">&#x3C;img src="logo.jpg"\n  width="150" height="150" />\n</code></pre>\n<p>Another important attribute is <code>alt</code>, which provides a text description in the browser in case the image doesn\'t load properly, as well as helping search engines and screen readers for visually disabled understand the meaning of the image. </p>\n<pre><code class="language-html">&#x3C;img src="images/cat.jpg"\n  alt="Mufasa sitting on top\n       of Pride Rock, looking \n       majestic." />\n</code></pre>\n',
